fr.inria.atlanmod.mogwai.mapping

Class NeoEMFMapping

  • Object
    • AbstractMapping
      • NeoEMFMapping
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EMFtoGraphMapping

    public final class NeoEMFMapping
extends AbstractMapping
implements EMFtoGraphMapping
    An implementation of EMFtoGraphMapping representing how NeoEMF maps EMF models into Blueprints databases.

    This mapping is based on the one implicitly defined in BlueprintsPersistenceBackend and DirectWriteBlueprintsStore. It will be externalized in a future version of NeoEMF to provide more flexibility on the EMF to Blueprints mapping.

    The current version of NeoEMF (1.0.1) doesn't contain class hierarchy within the database. This lack of metaclass-level information avoid the definition of allOfKind(String) and isKindOf(Vertex, String) that throw UnsupportedOperationException. This will be fixed in a future version of NeoEMF.

    Author:
    Gwendal DANIEL
    See Also:
    BlueprintsPersistenceBackend, DirectWriteBlueprintsStore, AbstractMapping, EMFtoGraphMapping

      • newInstance

        public Object newInstance(String typeName,
                          String typePackageNsURI,
                          String resourceName)
                   throws NullPointerException
        Creates a new instance of the type typeName and add it to the resource resourceName.

        typePackageNsURI can be provided for mappings that support metaclasses defined in multiple EPackages. Note that this information may be optional or mandatory, depending on the mapping used.

        Specified by:
        newInstance in interface EMFtoGraphMapping
        Specified by:
        newInstance in class AbstractMapping
        Parameters:
        typeName - the name of the metaclass to create an instance of
        typePackageNsURI - the URI of the EPackage that defines the metaclass typeName
        resourceName - the name of the resource where the new element is stored
        Returns:
        an Object representing the created instance of typeName
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the provided typePackageNsURI is null (it is required by NeoEMF to create a new instance of a given type)
